      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. In a large pan, heat a generous amount of olive oil until shimmering, then add a substantial amount of minced garlic and cook until fragrant.\n2. While the garlic infuses the olive oil, cook your pasta according to package directions.\n3. Drain the pasta and immediately toss it into the pan with the garlic and olive oil, stirring constantly.\n4. Sprinkle in a heavy dose of chili flakes, ensuring they coat every strand of pasta, and continue to toss.\n5. Finally, add more garlic and a final drizzle of olive oil, then stir in the pasta until everything is perfectly coated with the spicy garlic flavor.",
